            "abstract": {
                "p": "The invention discloses an ultrahigh vacuum ion source wafer cleaning system comprising a sampling vacuum chamber, an ion-beam vacuum chamber and a magnetic force transmission rod, wherein the two vacuum chambers are connected by an isolating valve; a sampling valve, a vacuum pump and an observation glass window are arranged on the sampling vacuum chamber; an observation glass window, a vacuum pump, an infrared roasting lamp and a hydrogen ion source are arranged on the ion-beam vacuum chamber; the magnetic force transmission rod perforates through the sampling vacuum chamber and the ion-beam vacuum chamber and is provided with a removable substrate table with a bonding function, the magnetic force transmission rod can be used for transmitting the substrate table to the ion-beam vacuum chamber from the sampling vacuum chamber, and the iron source can be used for vertically cleaning wafers on the substrate table. Under ultrahigh vacuum environment, the ultrahigh vacuum ion source wafer cleaning system cleans the wafers by the low-energy hydrogen ion source and carries out wafer cold welding at normal temperature or in a slightly heating condition, and a plurality of wafers are bonded into a crystal block to obtain a low-loss doubling frequency crystal."
